[48;5;237m[38;5;231m## How Docs Become Code[39m                                                         [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mThe repo follows a four-stage pipeline. Every package passes through each stage[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m in order.[39m                                                                      [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m### Stage 1: Doc[39m                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mA README and boundary description exist. The package's purpose, ownership, and [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mnon-ownership are written down. No code.[39m                                        [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mThis stage is complete for all ten packages.[39m                                    [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m### Stage 2: Spec[39m                                                               [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mA canonical spec document defines the package's public API surface: exported [39m   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mtypes, factory functions, expected behavior contracts, error semantics, and [39m    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mintegration points with adjacent packages. The spec is detailed enough that an [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mengineer can implement against it without design questions.[39m                     [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mA spec is not a design doc. It is an implementation reference. It answers "what[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m does the code look like" not "why does this package exist."[39m                    [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m### Stage 3: Workflow[39m                                                           [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mA workflow document defines one narrow end-to-end slice through the package. It[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m names the exact types, functions, and call sequences involved. Workflows are [39m  [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mthe unit of implementation work — each one produces a shippable increment.[39m      [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m### Stage 4: Code[39m                                                               [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mTypeScript implementation, tests, and package.json. Code is written to satisfy [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231ma specific[39m                                                                      [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m… +2976 lines …[39m                                                                 [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m out the highest-risk contradictions that must be fixed immediately[39m             [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m5. define how to keep weekend examples spec-conformant[39m                          [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mEnd the file with SPEC_RECONCILIATION_RULES_READY.[39m                              [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m---[39m                                                                             [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mSTEP OWNER CONTRACT:[39m                                                            [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- You are the accountable owner for step "lead-reconciliation-rules".[39m           [49m
